channel.title: YouTube :(
channel.description:
Something is wrong with my computer or something, cause YouTube sort of quit of working. This is what displays every time I try to watch a video:
[img]http://img127.imageshack.us/img127/9443/22560017nt9.jpg[/img]
and on newer videos:
[img]http://img293.imageshack.us/img293/1087/76295834sg1.jpg[/img]
occasionally random videos will load and work, but the majority of YouTube doesn't. Also, if I click the option to watch a video in high quality (under views), I can watch it.
[img]http://img360.imageshack.us/img360/8826/35624077rh4.jpg[/img]
But that option is only on some (not that many) videos.
Not to mention, it's been like this for like 3 months.

item.title: YouTube :(
item.dc:creator: @jimmy0s Jimmy OS
item.description:
@jimmy0s wrote:

  1. I have tried reinstalling flash, did nothing.
  2. I have cleared my cookies, several times.
  3. I have waited, I’ve been waiting months
    hoping it might just be YouTube being weird.
    But it works on my dad’s laptop, so it isn’t
    just YouTube apparently.

I’ve tried my best to figure out what’s wrong
on my own, but I couldn’t, so I came here for
answers. Not to mention, right now not even
the high quality opt. videos are working. Which
sucks even more lol

item.title: YouTube :(
item.dc:creator: @Eh_Pretty_Easy Eh Pretty Easy
item.description:
@Eh_Pretty_Easy wrote:

There are a couple of reasons why the site won’t work, I’ll list some.

  1. Something wrong with your flash player, try reinstalling it.
  2. Clear your cookies, this exact same thing happened to me a couple months ago and doing that fixed it. Seems that for an unknown reason lots of cookies/internet cache slow down buffering videos.
  3. Just wait, see what happens.
